title: Andrea Lehane: Monkey bike accused back in police custody - Yahoo7
text:
Share Andrea Lehane: Monkey bike accused back in police custody - Yahoo7 A man charged over the ‘monkey bike’ hit and run crash, that claimed the life of a Melbourne woman in 2015, has once again been arrested by police. Close Monkey bike ‘killer’ arrested again after being repeatedly freed on bail UP NEXT VIDEO Monkey bike ‘killer’ arrested again after being repeatedly freed on bail. 7News Monkey bike ‘killer’ arrested again after being repeatedly freed on bail 
Caleb Jakobsson was arrested by police on Wednesday and faced an out-of-sessions court hearing. 
He’s been charged with possessing and using methamphetamine, handling stolen goods and breaching bail. Caleb Jakobsson. Picture: 7 News The Carrum Downs crash that claimed the life of Andrea Lehane. Picture: 7 News 
Jakobsson was a teenager in 2015 when he allegedly mowed down Andrea Lehane in the carpark of a Carrum Downs shopping centre and left her to die. 
It is not the first time Jakobsson has breached his bail, after he was originally released to live in country Victoria. Crash victim Andrea Lehane. Picture: 7 News 
Jakobsson admitted to police breaching that bail on numerous occasions, a court has heard. 
Last year, Victorian Police were frustrated when an application to revoke his bail was denied and Jakobsson was moved back to Melbourne to live with an aunt and uncle in Croydon. 
According to 7 News, police are hoping, thanks to stricter bail laws, that Jakobsson will be remanded in custody on the new charges. Caleb Jakobsson. Picture: 7 News
